      "role": "user",
      "content": "oh sorry, my bad. here is the text: \"4.2 PRICE ADJUSTMENTS: During peak demand months (defined as June-August), the Supplier reserves the right to implement a price adjustment of up to 5% per month to account for market volatility. Such adjustments shall be applied to all subsequent invoices without prior written notice to SwiftRoute.\"\n\ncan you confirm if this means they can just change the rates whenever they want without our approval? i really need to know if we're safe from sudden price spikes here.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
